```

Use the `useUnreadNotificationsList` hook to fetch paginated `UnreadNotifications` records:

```typescript
import { useUnreadNotificationsList } from "@/hooks/unreadNotifications";

function MyComponent() {
  const { data, isLoading, error } = useUnreadNotificationsList({
    page: 1,
    size: 20,
    sort: "-created_at",
  });

  if (isLoading) return <div>Loading...</div>;
  return (
    <div>
      {data?.data.map(item => <div key={String(item.id)}>{/* render */}</div>)}
    </div>
  );
}
```

The hook returns a `UnreadNotificationsPage` with `data`, `total`, `page`, `size`, `totalPages`.
It calls `GET /unread-notifications/pagination` internally.
